SIMPLE: pennyworth
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pennyworth
<hw>Pen"ny*worth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
penny's worth; as much as may be bought for a penny.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A dear
<xex>pennyworth</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: The full value of one's penny expended; due
return for money laid out; a good bargain; a bargain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The priests sold the better <qex>pennyworths</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A small quantity; a trifle.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penock</ent>⟦br⟧
